      "content": "i get that, and i'll definitely use that for my main points. but for the debate to be fair, i have to be able to anticipate the other team's logic. if they bring up the \"economic stability\" or \"community preservation\" angle, i can't just say 'no you're wrong'—i need to understand the actual thought process they'll use. \n\ncan u just walk me through the theoretical justifications used at the time? like, what were the specific economic or sociological theories that proponents used to argue that keeping neighborhoods homogenous or strictly zoned would prevent urban decay or protect property values? i just need the logical framework they'd use to move from 'segregation' to 'stability' for my rebuttal prep.",
